s\", \"from\": 350, \"to\": 357}, {\"ngram\": \"their medals\", \"from\": 365, \"to\": 377}, {\"ngram\": \"the podium\", \"from\": 387, \"to\": 397}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's why they do it.\", \"from\": 400, \"to\": 422, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"New Zealand rowers Ollie Maclean, Logan Ullrich, Tom Murray and Matt Macdonald chow down on the silver medals they won in the men's four.Photo:AFP/BERTRAND GUAY Back in the day, gold and other precious metals were used as a form of currency.\", \"from\": 424, \"to\": 666, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 424, \"end\": 435, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"score\": 0.9990690122722604, \"rank\": 0.0005199131649200679, \"text\": \"New Zealand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_Zealand_national_rugby_union_team\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the silver medals\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 533}, {\"ngram\": \"Photo:AFP/BERTRAND GUAY\", \"from\": 561, \"to\": 584}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 593, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 602, \"to\": 606}, {\"ngram\": \"other precious metals\", \"from\": 611, \"to\": 632}, {\"ngram\": \"a form\", \"from\": 646, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"currency\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 664}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When a person received a lump of gold, one way to check its authenticity was to bite into it.\", \"from\": 668, \"to\": 761, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a person\", \"from\": 673, \"to\": 681}, {\"ngram\": \"a lump\", \"from\": 691, \"to\": 697}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 701, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"one way\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 714}, {\"ngram\": \"its authenticity\", \"from\": 724, \"to\": 740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gold is softer than other metals, so if your teeth marks were visible, chances were good the gold was real.\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 869, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gold\", \"from\": 762, \"to\": 766}, {\"ngram\": \"other metals\", \"from\": 782, \"to\": 794}, {\"ngram\": \"your teeth marks\", \"from\": 802, \"to\": 818}, {\"ngram\": \"chances\", \"from\": 833, \"to\": 840}, {\"ngram\": \"the gold\", \"from\": 851, \"to\": 859}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the early days of the modern Olympics, gold medals were just that - pure gold.\", \"from\": 871, \"to\": 952, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the early days\", \"from\": 874, \"to\": 888}, {\"ngram\": \"the modern Olympics\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 911}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medals\", \"from\": 913, \"to\": 924}, {\"ngram\": \"just that - pure gold\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 951}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, that practice stopped in 1912, according to the International Olympic Committee.\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 1043, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1042, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that practice\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 976}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nowadays, medals are made of a silver compound, with a few grams of gold for the first-place winners.\", \"from\": 1045, \"to\": 1146, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 1055, \"to\": 1061}, {\"ngram\": \"a silver compound\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1091}, {\"ngram\": \"a few grams\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1109}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1113, \"to\": 1117}, {\"ngram\": \"the first-place winners\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1145}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year's medals alsoeach contain a tiny piece of iron from past refurbishments of the Eiffel Tower.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1250, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This year's medals\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1166}, {\"ngram\": \"a tiny piece\", \"from\": 1184, \"to\": 1196}, {\"ngram\": \"iron\", \"from\": 1200, \"to\": 1204}, {\"ngram\": \"past refurbishments\", \"from\": 1210, \"to\": 1229}, {\"ngram\": \"the Eiffel Tower\", \"from\": 1233, \"to\": 1249}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So if the medals are no longer pure gold, why do athletes continue to gnaw on them?\", \"from\": 1252, \"to\": 1335, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the medals\", \"from\": 1258, \"to\": 1268}, {\"ngram\": \"pure gold\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1292}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1301, \"to\": 1309}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The answer, according to the International Olympic Committee, is simple: Because photographers ask them to.\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1444, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1366, \"end\": 1397, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The answer\", \"from\": 1337, \"to\": 1347}, {\"ngram\": \"photographers\", \"from\": 1418, \"to\": 1431}]}, {\"sentence\": \"David Wallechinsky, the president of the International Society of Olympic Historians, previously told CNN the shot had become an \\\"obsession\\\" among photographers.\", \"from\": 1446, \"to\": 1607, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1446, \"end\": 1464, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"David Wallechinsky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/David_Wallechinsky\"}, {\"begi